               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-273-person2569">
                  ROBERT 
                  HOWSON
               <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2569" type="surname" value="HOWSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2569" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2569" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 9th of August, about nine o'clock in the evening, I was at the top of Cow-lane with a female; I felt my handkerchief go from my coat pocket - I turned, and saw the prisoner give it to another; I followed them. but the other got off - I followed the prisoner to Fleet-market - he began to run; I called Stop thief! and he was secured - I have no doubt he saw me; he stopped himself when I cried Stop thief! I am sure he gave the handkerchief to the other - I was quite sober.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Where did you take me into custody? A. In Fleet-market; I did not take the other because I wished to secure you both if possible; you attempted to get away, but could not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-273-person2570">
                  JAMES 
                  SLATE
               <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2570" type="surname" value="SLATE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2570" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2570" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prisoner was brought into the watch-house a little after nine o'clock - he had nothing on him but a little iron screw-driver and a handkerchief, which he said was his own.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in <placeName id="t18290910-273-crimeloc1507">Cow-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-273-crimeloc1507" type="placeName" value="Cow-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290910-273-crimeloc1507" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-273-off1505 t18290910-273-crimeloc1507"></join>, and saw this gentleman take notice of me - I went on my way down to Fleet-market; I heard some person cry Stop thief! or Stop him! I stopped, and went back towards the prosecutor - I took out my own handkerchief while I was passing the gentleman, and wiped my face with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-273-person2571">
                  ROBERT 
                  HOWSON
               <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2571" type="surname" value="HOWSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2571" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-person2571" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My handkerchief was a red one, and this is green - I did not see the prisoner take it out, but I saw him with it; he gave it to the other, who turned off to the right - when I got to the turning, the other was out of sight; I am sure it was my property - I had used it a few minutes before; it was a fine night, and just twilight.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290910-273-verdict1508" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290910-273-verdict1508" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
